3. The “copycat attractor” you mentioned

That’s actually a real phenomenon.

In systems theory it resembles mimetic dynamics.

People imitate behaviors that appear:

successful
popular
high-status
emotionally intense

Examples:
	•	fashion trends
	•	viral memes
	•	financial bubbles
	•	mass panic
	•	copycat crimes

The attractor forms when the feedback loop is:

visibility → imitation → more visibility

In Meaning Physics we could formalize this as:

Replication force

or

Mimetic attractor


